    <item rdf:about="http://fink.sourceforge.net/news/#2006-03-03%20Problem%20with%20Apple's%20Security%20Update%202006-001">
      <title>Problem with Apple's Security Update 2006-001</title>
      <link>http://fink.sourceforge.net/news/#2006-03-03%20Problem%20with%20Apple's%20Security%20Update%202006-001</link>
      <guid>http://fink.sourceforge.net/news/#2006-03-03%20Problem%20with%20Apple's%20Security%20Update%202006-001</guid>
      <description>
      <p>
The Fink team has received reports of problems with the rsync
program which was modified by Apple's new Security Update 2006-001: for some
users, fink selfupdate fails to function after the Security
Update.  (The underlying cause appears to be a problem with the 
--delete option for rsync.)
</p>
      <p>
As a workaround, users can run fink install rsync to use
fink's rsync package rather than the Apple program.  Or, for those users
who need specific features of the Apple program (such as support for
Extended Attributes), another workaround is fink selfupdate-cvs
to switch from rsync to cvs updating.  
</p>
<p>Update 3/13/06: This has been resolved by security update 2006-002,
<a href="http://docs.info.apple.com/article.html?artnum=303453">according
to Apple's documentation</a>.
</p>
    </description>
      <content:encoded>
      <p>
The Fink team has received reports of problems with the rsync
program which was modified by Apple's new Security Update 2006-001: for some
users, fink selfupdate fails to function after the Security
Update.  (The underlying cause appears to be a problem with the 
--delete option for rsync.)
</p>
      <p>
As a workaround, users can run fink install rsync to use
fink's rsync package rather than the Apple program.  Or, for those users
